imagecat-rails.title: Create an ansible playbook to install dependencies of this application
Add Test Coverage report to CI

comments.body:
Once you have the rails gem installed, you can type `rails new --help` to see options. Ones to pay particular attention to include:
- `--database=postgresql`
- `--skip-test` (this is because we will be using rspec rather than the builtin test framework)
- You may want to look at the `--javascript` option - the default is importmap. I think our other applications are using Vite, but that is not an option to start the application with. 
- You may also want to look at the `--css` option - I think our other projects use bootstrap, but I don't know whether they're set up the same way as `rails new` with that flag does it.

@sandbergja might have better ideas about the javascript and css options, and @bess might suggest that you skip some of these flags altogether.
